race.comment: SUNSPRITE (12) made solid inroads over 1300m at Randwick Kensington on debut, beaten 2.5L. Was expected to need the outing and is sure to keep improving for a leading metro stable. Draws well enough, and she sits at the bottom of the handicap. Stablemate ROYAL CHIC (1) impressed at Eagle Farm in Stakes grade earlier in the year and will have taken fitness and learning from her first-up outing. She's still a work in progress but jumps from a soft gate and the 3kg claim brings her into it. Trust is required but she has the ability. SUPERATA (2) rates well enough off threatening efforts at Scone and Taree, and JVO can use the inside barrier to his advantage. Waller-trained SALT SPRAY (9) has his second start and will have taken fitness and learning away from Warwick Farm. A likely improver.
